cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Optimizing Nemotron-3-Super-120B on DGX Spark: Breaking the 14-TPS Bottleneck"
message: "If you use this optimization methodology or benchmark data, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Rawat"
    given-names: "Rajendra Singh"
    affiliation: "cogni.chat"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0007-5017-1341"
repository-code: "https://github.com/airawatraj/dgx-spark-nemotron-super-agent"
abstract: >-
  A technical implementation and benchmarking suite for running Nemotron-3-Super-120B
  as an autonomous agent on a personal NVIDIA DGX Spark. This repository documents
  the methodology for achieving 23.2+ TPS using NVFP4 Marlin quantization,
  speculative decoding, and kernel-level sandboxing via OpenShell/K3s.
keywords:
  - "Nemotron"
  - "DGX Spark"
  - "vLLM"
  - "AI Agents"
  - "NVFP4"
  - "Performance Benchmarking"
